Program: Discovery
Title: Why do women outlive men
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0123663
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 30 Dec 2012
Baby girls born today in the UK can expect to live to 82 years old, whereas boys on average will die 4 years earlier. Evolutionary biologist Dr Yan Wong looks at the latest evidence suggesting that where ageing is concerned, men seem to be at a genetic disadvantage. From research on ancient Korean eunuchs to laboratory fruit flies, new studies seek the answer to why males across the animal kingdom live faster and die younger. So, is the gender gap here to stay? Show less